description: Check this great looking poster out from Munster Studio done for our August 2013 Tour across Europe. 18" x 24", 4 colors, limited to 68 copies, signed and numbered.

description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. Here's the excellent tour poster from the string of dates we did with Metz and Titus Andronicus this year. Design by wethreeclub. 16.5" x 23.5"

description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. 18" x 24" poster 100lb quality stock. Designed and printed by Doublenaut.

description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. This thing rules and Fucked Up collectors definitely need it. 24" x 36"

name: Poster - Fucked Up vs. Iron Age, 2007
description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. A poster for some shows we did in Texas with Iron Age. I'm pretty Iron Age wins in this so-called "epic battle" every time. Design by Neolithic. 22" x 10"

name: Poster - Buffalo @ Mohawk Place w/ Psychadelic Horseshie
description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. From Oct 25, 2008. 13" x 25".

name: Poster - Toronto @ Opera House w/ Kurt Vile
description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. One of the only known depictions of the mysterious David Eliade... One of my personal faves. From Feb 26, 2010. Note: these have some wear and tear around the edges - creases, etc... But poster still looks great. 14" x 24"

description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. From Feb 16, 2010. 18" x 24".

name: Poster - Brighton @ Coalition, Nov 16 2012
description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. Really cool black and white poster bringing together some themes in David Comes to Life and Damian's propensity for self-harm. Note: these posters are a bit frayed at the edges due to wear and tear, but still look great. 16.5" x 23.5" Design by Dan Bowden.

name: Poster - Detroit @ Magic Stick w/ Wavves
description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. A poster from our show with Wavves at the Magic Stick in Detroit on Sept 30, 2011. 25" x 19". Please note, this poster has a shitload of swastikas on it. Obviously our band dislikes nazis and most of us dislike the queen as well. Is this poster saying she is a nazi? Equivalent to a nazi? Dunno, it's art, deal with it. Just wanted to let you know and just saying, if you're from Germany, we take no responsibility for what happens if you order this poster. Design by fugscrens

name: Poster - Chicago @ Logan Square w/ Wavves
description: Before ordering posters please read about poster shipping. Poster for a show with Wavves at Logan Square in Chicago on Sept 29, 2011. 22" x 20". Design by Kill Hatsumomo Prints.

name: Daytrotter 7"
description: Tracks: Magic Word/David Comes To Life/Crooked Head Three reworked originals recorded live off the floor for a 'Daytrotter Session' at the famous all-analog studio in Rock Island, Illinois. Released in numerous variations for Record Store Day and in limited quantity with a single cover.

name: Crooked Head 7"
description: Tracks: Crooked Head/I Hate Summer Single for Chemistry of Common Life. The LP track and an original B side.

name: Police 7"
description: Tracks: Police/Municipal Prick Our second record, released all the way back in 2003. And we still play this song. Every show. I hate my life.

name: Year of the Pig 7" - UK Press
description: Tracks: Year of The Pig (edit)/For My Friends A reworking and remixing of the 18 minute track of the same name by Eric Broucek backed with a cover of the C86 classic "Anorak City" by Another Sunny Day.

name: Couple Tracks 7"
description: Tracks: Couple Tracks/Heir Apparent Originally available only with advanced purchase of the COUPLE TRACKS LP/CD. Limited single that has not been specifically for sale other than from the band on tour. Two exclusive original tracks.

name: Metal Button/Pin/Badge
description: Check out these nice metal pins made by our buddy Diego in Mexico City.  They have two little clips on the back for easy fastening to your backpack, hat, sweater, butt flap, etc.

name: Beanie aka Toque aka Winter Hat
description: This is the first Fucked Up headgear ever.  Just in time for the (second half) of winter.

name: Queen of Hearts Shirt
description: Here's a new shirt that we've been told has a Social Distortion-y feel, a first for us. Inspired by the song of the same name and designed by Jason Gilmore. Printed on Peace and Cotton brand shirts.

name: Triumph of Life Shirt
description: An oldie but a goodie.  Printed on Peace and Cotton brand t-shirts.

name: Lady Shirt
description: T-Shirt brand:  Fruit of the Loom

name: Letters Shirt - White
description: Everyone always seems to want to buy our shirts more if they say the band name on it, which we think is a little gauche, but we've sold out so hard that we'll pretty much do anything to make a buck.  Including putting our band name on a t-shirt in really big letters.  Printed on very nice Peace and Cotton brand shirts.

name: Letters Shirt - Black
description: Printed on very nice Peace and Cotton brand shirts.

name: Year of the Tiger 12"
description:
Year of the Tiger b/w ONNO.

Instalment #5 of the Zodiac series.

Fucked Up, Austra, Jim Jarmusch, Duchess Says.

Soon to be appearing as a children's book.

Truth

name: David / Veronica SHIRT
description: This shirt was designed by Jason Gilmore and is printed on Gildan Soft. The shirt says "Watch the tower as it starts to teeter. New lyrics follow the same old meter."

name: Fucked Up / Sloan Christmas 7"
description: So... Christmas. We missed it. We were only to get 50 of these in time for our xmas shows in Toronto on Dec 20 & 21, 2011. If you didn't get one there, they are exclusively available right here. On Side A, Fucked Up plays "Jingle Bells", on Side B, Sloan plays The 12 Days of Xmas. Limited to 500 copies. All proceeds from the sale of this record go to the COUNTERfit Drug Users Memorial Project and the Barriere Lake Legal Defense Fund.

name: Tote Bag
description: Here's a handy bag to put all your FU collectibles in..

name: Fucked Up / Wavves T-Shirt
description: Limited Edition Fucked Up / Wavves Tour T-shirt. Our friends at Mishka made this shirt for us and Wavves when we toured the U.S. together. It's printed on Mishka brand shirt which is some high-quality cotton.

name: Lightbulb Sweatshirt
description: Our first ever sweatshirt (or "crewshirt").  Printed on Gildan.  The lighbulb is on the back and the logo on the front, if you couldn't tell.

name: Lightbulb T-Shirt
description: If you like David Comes to Life, then you'll definitely like this shirt, which has a lightbulb on the front (add a small logo on the back).  Printed on Fruit of the Loom shirts.

name: FU Sunglasses
description: Yeah, we went there.  See the world through the eyes of Fucked Up.

name: FU / Haymaker split 7"
description: The record you love to love or love to hate.  Released on Deep Six.

name: Sail Shirt
description: Printed on Froot of the Loom

name: Logo Shirt - Black w/ Silver Logo
description: Printed on Fruit of the Loom

name: David Comes to Life 2xLP
description: Tracks: Let Her Rest/Queen of Hearts/Under My Nose/The Other Shoe/Turn the Season/Running On Nothing/Remember My Name/A Slanted Tone/Serve Me Right/Truth I Know/Life In Paper/Ship of Fools/A Little Death/I Was There/Inside a Frame/The Recursive Girl/One More Night/Lights Go Up You know what it is.

name: David Comes to Life CD
description: Tracks: Let Her Rest/Queen of Hearts/Under My Nose/The Other Shoe/Turn the Season/Running On Nothing/Remember My Name/A Slanted Tone/Serve Me Right/Truth I Know/Life In Paper/Ship of Fools/A Little Death/I Was There/Inside a Frame/The Recursive Girl/One More Night/Lights Go Up Our best record, no joke.

name: Year of the Rat 12"
description: Tracks: Year of the Rat/First Born 3rd in the series of releases coinciding with the Chinese Zodiac. 'Rat' is a Krautrock-influenced 12 minute blast with a massive finish. Recorded in the same studio as "What's The Story, Morning Glory?" in London and mixed in Toronto. The b-side is an original which treads somewhere between ugly glam and an FU take on Thin Lizzy style guitar harmonies.

name: Mixtape 4 (Cassette)
description: When people see us selling tapes at our shows they're always like, "what's on this?", so here: SIDE A 1) “Son the Father” Intro Performed live at the Opera House Toronto, Feb 26 2010 2) “The Other Shoe” From the David Comes to Life album 3) Jennifer Castle “Powers” From the album Castlemusic 4) Animal Man “Do You Feed?” From the David’s Town album 5) Mad Men “Wax World” From some random Mad Men demo 6) “B” From various bits of the FU discography 7) “The Lurking Fear” Live at CIUT radio, Toronto, sometime in 2001 8) “Heir Apparent” From the Couple Tracks 7” single 9) “Maxwell’s Banter” Performed live at Maxwell’s, Hoboken NY, Feb 18 2010 10) “Ballad Of Hammerhead” From the forthcoming Best Show on WFMU DVD 11) Ben Rayner and the Pricks “Slovakian Pete” From the Butlins Sessions SIDE B 1) “Here Lies Are” From the split 12” with Serena Maneesh 2) “Truth I Know” snippet From the David Comes to Life album 3) Interview Banter Taken from Vish Khanna’s hilarious CBC Radio 3 internet show 4) Young Governor “I Heart Summer” From the Summer Girl 7” 5) “Year of the Tiger” snippet From the Year of the Tiger 12” single 6) “What Would you Do (For Veronica)?” From the Do All Words Can Do 7” single 7) “Son the Father” Taken from the 2009 Polaris awards Gala 8) “Two Snakes” Performed live at the Opera House, Toronto, Feb 26 2010 9) Gerry and the Pacemakers “You’ll Never Walk Alone” From the You’ll Never Walk Alone 45rpm single

name: David's Plan 7"
description: Tracks: David's Plan/Do They Know it's Christmas? Second single released specifically for charities (First was David's Christmas) -- this one towards helping missing and murdered aboriginal women in Canada -- has an original on the A-side and a star studded cover of "Do They Know It's Christmas?" on the flip. Guest appearances by: Ezra Koenig, Bob Mould, David Cross, Tegan and Sara, GZA, Andrew WK, Kevin Drew, Kyp Malone, Yo La Tengo. Recording and production was facilitated entirely by our winnings at the Polaris Prize. 100% of the proceeds from the sale of this record go to the group Missing Justice in Montreal and the Power of Women group in Vancouver.

name: Royal Swan 7"
description: Tracks: Royal Swan/I'm Sick by Katie Stelmanis Split with local ally Katie Stelmanis, originally given away at our 12-Hour marathon concert in NYC in 2008. Royal Swan is a track from ChemCom and features Stelmanis vocals. I'm Sick is a Stelmanis original.

name: Records Shirt
description:
Lots of records, but on a shirt.  Designed by our buddy Zach.

T-Shirt brand:  Fruit of the Loom

name: Crowd Shirt
description: T-shirt brand:  Fruit of the Loom

name: Logo Shirt - Black w/ Gold Logo
description: T-shirt brand:  Fruit of the Loom

name: FU Fist Shirt
description: Designed by Seripop.  Also sold at soundscreen.com

name: No Epiphany 7"
description: Tracks: No Epiphany/No Epiphany Remix by No Age The LP track pressed to 45 backed by an experimental reordering and remixing by the California heavies, NO AGE.

name: Litany 7"
description: Tracks: Litany/What Could Have Been/Colour Removal/Reset the Ride 5th official release by the band and our first real EP. 4 tracks about repetition and cyclicality with more than willing nods to early UK punk and possible motorcycles. Most impressive, the sleeve folds out into a massive 12 panel collage pieced together by 10kMarbs a la Crucifix/Crass/Winston Smith. One of the most substantial singles in the discography.

name: Year of the Ox 12"
description: Tracks: Year Of The Ox/Solomon's Song 4th in a series of releases coinciding with the Chinese Zodiac. 'Ox' is a 13-minute song backed by a string quartet. B Side is another FU original featuring a number of local guests an auxiliary instruments, including a dark, film noir style saxophone intro by Aerin Fogel of the Bitters.

name: Year of the Dog 12"
description: Tracks: Year of The Dog/Last Man Standing 1st in the series of releases coinciding with the Chinese Zodiac. 'Dog' is an expansive and plodding track, simplistically recorded and featuring some questionably legitimate forays into recorder and xylophone playing. The flip is a re-recorded song from the FU demo, given the royal treatment. The record is double grooved, so depending on where you drop the needle you'll get one of two possble versions of each song, one of which was recorded pushing the entire mix through a SOLDANO guitar amplifier.

name: Year of the Pig 12"
description: Tracks: Year of The Pig/Black Hats 2nd in the series of releases coinciding with the Chinese Zodiac. 'Pig' is an explosive quarter of an hour tract reminiscent of Pink Floyd, Led Zeppelin and Neu! Features guest vocals by Jennifer Castle (Castlemusic), piano and organ by Max McCabe (Deadly Snakes). Original b-side.

name: Dangerous Fumes 7"
description: Tracks: Dangerous Fumes/Fixed Race(?) Somewhere between early FU and FU "after the fall" this track was originally meant to appear on and be a single for Hidden World. Instead this is a stand alone single in the stockpile. Fast and loud with singing leads and "breathing" for back up vocals.

name: Dance of Death 7"
description: Tracks: Dance of Death/Zezozose This was the first record Young Guv was on, singing back-ups, like 5 years before he joined the band. And the B-side is named after Charles Manson's son.

name: Year of the Pig CD
description: Tracks: Year of The Pig/The Black Hats/Year of The Pig (Us Edit)/Mustaa Lunta/Year of The Pig (UK Edit)/Anorak City/Year of The Pig (Japan Edit)/For My Friends A collection of all the variations of Year of the Pig -- the original release, and the three 7" versions -- with all of the original artwork.

name: Epics in Minutes CD
description: Tracks: Colour Removal/What Could've Been/Baiting The Public I/Baiting The Public II/Last Man Standing/Litany/Police/Circling the Drain/Reset The Ride/A Light That Never Comes On/Generation+Red/Dance of Death/Live on CIUT/Full First Demo Epics In Minutes is a compilation of early singles by the band. “This is the closest that there will ever be to a Fucked Up retrospective.” Some of the versions on this compilation are different than the ones that were originally released on the singles.

name: Hidden World 2xLP
description: Tracks: Crusades/David Comes to Life/Invisible Leader/Carried Out to The Sea/Baiting The Public/Fate of Fates/Two Snakes/Hidden World/Manqueller Man/Blaze of Glory/Triumph of Life/Jacob's Ladder/Vivian Girls First full length release from 2006. This release touches on the bands more experimental ambitions and is firm in the immediacy of their early tracks. Heavy with melodic indie pop undertones and intricate and varied guitar work.

name: Couple Tracks 2xLP
description: Track Listing: DISC ONE - THE HARD STUFF 1. No Pasaran (A-side of first 7", Deranged, 2002) 2. Neat Parts (7" Version) (B-side of Triumph Of Life 7", Peter Bower, 2006) 3. Generation (7" Version) (A-side of Generation 7", Slasher, 2005) 4. Ban Violins (B-side of Generation 7", Slasher, 2005) 5. Dangerous Fumes (A-side of Dangerous Fumes 7", self-released, 2005) 6. Triumph Of Life (7" Version) (A-side of Triumph Of Life 7", Peter Bower, 2006) 7. Fixed Race (B-side of Humos Peligrosos 7", La Vida Es Un Mus, 2006) 8. Toronto FC (from Hard Skin split 7", No Future, 2007) 9. Black Hats (B-side of Year Of The Pig 12", What's Your Rupture?, 2006) 10. David Christmas (A-side of David Christmas 7", Hidden World, 2007) 11. No Epiphany (Fast Version) (unreleased Chemistry Of Common Life outtake, intended for No Epiphany 7", Matador, 2009) 12. Crooked Head (Video Version) (unreleased edit of track from Chemistry Of Common Life, 2008) DISC TWO - THE FUN STUFF 1. I Hate Summer (B-side of Crooked Head 7", Matador, 2008) 2. Teenage Problems (B-side of Dangerous Fumes 7", self-released, 2005) 3. Carried Out To Sea (unreleased demo version of song from Hidden World, 2006) 4. Looking Back (B-side of Shop Assistants 7", self-released giveaway at Toronto show, 2006) 5. Anorak City (Another Sunny Day cover, B-side of Year Of The Pig UK edit 7", Matador, 2008) 6. I Don't Want To Be Friends With You (A-side of Shop Assistants 7", self-released giveaway at Toronto show, 2006) 7. Mustaa Lunta (B-side of Year Of The Pig Japanese edit 7", Matdaor, 2008) 8. Dream Come True (B-side of Dolly Mixture 7", self-released giveaway at Toronto show, 2006) 9. Magic Kingdom (B-side of Generation 7", Slasher, 2005) 10. Magic Word (Daytrotter Version) (unreleased version of Chemistry Of Common Life song from Daytrotter Session, 2008) 11. Last Man Standing (Year Of The Dog Version) (from Year Of The Dog 12", Blocks Recording Club, 2006) 12. He's So Frisky (A-side of Dolly Mixture 7", self-released giveaway at Toronto show, 2006) 13. David Comes To Life (Daytrotter Version) (unreleased version of Hidden World song from Daytrotter Session, 2008) Couple Tracks spans an extraordinarily varied (and extraordinarily collectible) musical career that has mainly been documented on 7-inch vinyl singles released around the world on many labels in many countries. Chronologically, it ranges from the A-side of our first single, No Pasarán, a commentary on the Spanish Civil War released on Deranged in 2002, to the fast alternate take of No Epiphany.

name: The Chemistry of Common Life 2xLP
description: Tracks: Son the Father/Magic Word/Golden Seal/Days of Last/Crooked Head/No Epiphany/Black Albino Bones/Royal Swan/Twice Born/Looking For God/Chemistry of Common Life 2008 full length which won the Polaris Prize for music in Canada. More compositional and sweeping, psychedelic guitar work, but this time with a much better focus and well structured songwriting. Includes two instrumental tracks and the notorious "Son The Father." Some of the best FU songs to date.

name: Hidden World CD
description: Tracks: Crusades/David Comes to Life/Invisible Leader/Carried Out to The Sea/Baiting The Public/Fate of Fates/Two Snakes/Hidden World/Manqueller Man/Blaze of Glory/Triumph of Life/Jacob's Ladder/Vivian Girls First full length release from 2006. name: Halloween Weekend '07 DVD
description: Pro shot and edited video document of all the bands that played the Fucked Up Halloween Weekend in 2007. Full sets from Fucked Up and three songs each from all bands that played each night. Featuring performances by Brutal Knights, dd/mm/yyyy, Cold World, Career Suicide, Marvelous Darlings, Omegas, Statues, the Tranzmitors, Castle Music and many others.  Produced by Greg Benedetto.

name: David Comes to Life Postcard Set
description: So these are 5 postcards - on the front of each you get a character from DCTL and a bit of their story, on the back you get some space to write something important, and put a stamp on it and send it to someone.  Steam!

name: The Other Shoe 7"
description: Tracks: The Other Shoe / The Truest Road We released this record because there was a spare song that didn't fit anywhere - it's called The Truest Road, it's about Nick Fenstle, a Stirnerist / judge / factory owner / lawyer / Veronica's ****** / energy drink entrepreneur / Josh's dad. Also: ONE PER CUSTOMER! If you order more than one, you will get a refund (minus what paypal skims off) & no record. Thx.

name: Melvins / Fucked Up Split 12"
description:
LIMIT ONE PER PERSON.  IF YOU ORDER MORE THAN ONE YOUR ORDER WILL BE REFUNDED.

The Melvins are legit heroes to us and we were thrilled to be doing this record with them.  Here are some details care of Amphetamine Reptile:

Vol. 8  Melvins "Sugar Daddy Splits" - 33 1/3 rpm 12" w/ Fucked Up

The eighth release in this 13 volume series has Melvins "Rat Faced Granny" (live from Sugar Daddy LP) on the A-Side and Side One with Fucked Up's "21st Century Cling-Ons".

Mackie designed silk screened sleeve by Obsolete Industries. Hand stamped Vol. # on back side. This comes in a heavy duty 8mil polyvinyl sleeve (made for picture discs so you get to view your purdy splat color vinyl).

Edition of 700.

name: David / Veronica 7"
description: Tracks: Do All Words Can Do / What Would You Do (For Veronica)? Songs about David Eliade and Veronica Boisson, how cute. (FYI this record came in Matador's BEGN package)

name: Byrdesdale Garden City 7"
description: Tracks: Byrdesdale Garden City / Into the Light Fucked Up wrote some songs about that place where all the David's Town bands are from. They're real good. (FYI this record came in Matador's BEGN package)

name: Vivian / Octavio 7"
description: Tracks: Remember Me (That's All I Ask) / What They Didn't Know Some revealing stuff about Vivian Benson, the best character in DCTL on this one. Also we add a pinch of confusion (for good measure) with a track about Octavio. (FYI this record came in Matador's BEGN package)

name: Octavio Made The Bomb 7"
description: Tracks: Octavio Made The Bomb All is revealed! Find out who made the bomb, who ordered the fries, and what word rhymes with self. (FYI this record came in Matador's BEGN package)

name: Fucked Up / The Dirtbombs 7"
description: This record came out for the 2012 Bruise Cruise where Josh wasn't allowed on the boat and was literally shivering outside the Bahamas airport all night.  Most depressing Caribbean vacation.  Here we have FU with "I Hate Summer" and The Dirtbombs with "If can can can't we?" which makes a lot of sense given the circumstances.

name: Serena Maneesh Split 12"
description: Tracks: Here Lies Are/Opium Priest by Serena Maneesh Split 12" collaboration with Norwegian "nu-gaze" greats Serena Maneesh. Both tracks are exclusive to this release.

name: Japanese Singles CD
description: Tracks: A slightly more comprehensive "Epics In Minutes" for the Japanese market. Updated to include the Triumph of Life, Dangerous Fumes, and Generation 7"s and released by the legendary Japanese HC label HG FACT. 1000 pressed in Japan only, not available in North America (other than here)

name: Year of the Pig 7" - Japanese Press
description: Tracks: Year of The Pig (edit)/For My Friends A reworking and remixing of the 18 minute track of the same name by 10k'bles backed with a cover of local singer and FU collaborator Jennifer Castle.

name: Mixtape 2 (Cassette)
